          <msContents>
            <summary>Text praising one thousand names of the Hindu deity Śiva, especially his passive form as Sadāśiva, to be used in private or public devotion and worship (pūjā) of Śiva and positing him as the highest reality in the universe. Presented as a dialogue between the deity Kṛṣṇa and the legendary figures Mārkaṇḍeya and Vyāsā.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Śivasahasranāmastotra</title>
              <title type="vernacular">शिवसहस्रनामस्तोत्र</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīpadmapurāṇe uttarabhāge bilvakeścarek kṛṣṇamārkaṃḍeyavyāsādisaṃvāde ekonavatitamedhyāyeśrīśivasahasranāmastotraṃ saṃpūrṇaṃ // śrīsāṃbasadāśivārpaṇamastu // cha // cha // cha // (f. 29v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
